[Tech_AlienFacilityLead X2TechTemplate]
LongDescription="Although it was a time-intensive process, I was able to successfully decrypt the ADVENT data recovered by our troops in the field. As expected, the information includes the exact coordinates for one of ADVENT's remote facilities. With this knowledge in hand, we should be able to deploy a strike team to infiltrate and destroy the facility. I have no doubts that the loss of this site will deal a significant blow to the aliens' efforts. R. Tygan."

[BasicResearchProject X2TechTemplate]
DisplayName="Basic Research"
Summary="Rather than pursue a specific project, we can spend a period of time focusing on improving our theoretical understanding of alien technologies and the previously unknown physical laws that they imply. It will not be a brief effort, but when finished, we will be more efficient in our future research efforts. This is a project we can repeat multiple times."
CodeName="Fundamentals"
LongDescription="At this end of this research effort, we feel like we have achieved a better framework to ground our future pursuits. The implications of things like faster-than-light travel, psionics and genetic recoding are staggering, but in the here and now, we believe we have lowered some of the barriers to future research, and we should be able to survive with fewer scientific personnel than some tasks previously required. R. Tygan."
UnlockedDescription="The required number of scientists has been reduced by one for research projects, and research will accumulate at a faster rate than before."

[BasicEngineeringProject X2TechTemplate]
DisplayName="Engineering Research"
Summary="Our team can set aside specific goals to pursue general improvements in our overall ability to develop, test and manufacture hardware here on the Avenger. It will take some time, but when finished, Shen and her team should be able to do more with less. This is a project we can repeat multiple times."
CodeName="Foundations"
LongDescription="Working closely with Chief Engineer Shen, we've made significant strides in improving our ability to standardize our engineering practices on board the ship. This has allowed Shen and her people to overcome certain obstacles that previously appeared to require a larger staff to handle. R. Tygan."
UnlockedDescription="The required number of engineers has been reduced by one for many engineering projects."

[LaserWeapons X2TechTemplate]
DisplayName="Laser Weapons"
Summary="Using our new understanding of magnetism and the alien elerium substance, we should be able develop designs for powerful laser weaponry."
CodeName="Linebacker"
LongDescription="By studying the methods used by the aliens to manage energy consumption and heat dissipation in their weapons, we've built a working prototype of what we're calling a pulsed laser weapon, although some of the troops prefer to call them 'blasters' for reasons that are obscure to me. The power we are able to put through these weapons is immense, but the system cannot maintain a continuous beam of such immense energies, so it insted relies on a series of picosecond-long pulses of intense energy density to break down any chemical bonds the beam encounters. These weapons should be more accurate and do more damage, on average, than the ballistic weapons we have been using, although they don't quite match the firepower of the weaponry we have seen the aliens operating. R. Tygan."
UnlockedDescription="Prototype added to inventory"

[AdvancedLasers X2TechTemplate]
DisplayName="Advanced Laser Weapons"
Summary="With the basics of combat laser technology fully understood, we believe we can now develop specialized weapons for the troops."
CodeName="Fulcrum"
LongDescription="With a fuller understanding of laser weapon technology thanks to feedback from the troops and the engineering team, we were able to refine our weapon designs with a variety of changes to optics, pulse rate and capacitors to develop a series of specialty weapons usable in a variety of roles in the field. R. Tygan."
UnlockedDescription="Prototype added to inventory"

[Coilguns X2TechTemplate]
DisplayName="Coilguns"
CodeName="Laertes"
Summary="It is now time to move beyond reverse-engineering captured weapons to develop a new line of magnetic weaponry superior to what ADVENT utilizes."
LongDescription="The principles of coil-type magnetic weapons have long been known, but it has taken our understanding of alien materials and energy supplies to make that a reality. And the reality is we have developed weaponry that exceeds the firepower of ADVENT troops and approaches that of some alien weaponry.\n\nHowever, to call our newest standard-issue assault rifles \"coilguns\" is a bit of a misnomer. Coil technologies are notorious for accepting projectiles made out of ferromagnetic materials with precise shapes that do not allow adequate penetration and a lower rate of fire compared to our magnetic rifles. However, Shen and her colleagues found a workaround by making a hexagonal magnetic grouping surrounding the barrel, unlike our previous iteration of two parallel magnetic rails. The actual term for this is a linear induction weapon, but our forces insist on calling theirs coilguns or coil-rifles regardless, mainly because \"select-firing linear induction railgun\" does not roll off one's tongue adequately.\n\nWe believe that such problems regarding coil technologies would no longer be a problem when we begin our research into precision rifles and designated marksman rifles based on this new weapon design, but it bears attention regardless.\n\nAs for our projectile issue, Shen decided to create a specialized composite ablative penetrator to accompany our new intermediate 6.8x43mm ammunition. According to our calculations, this composite material would have minimal magnetic disruption and be sturdy enough to penetrate standard ADVENT armor within 500 meters. While thicker armor plating wielded by specialized ADVENT infantry and alien forces would still be able to withstand the penetrator, it would still be enough to reduce their effectiveness. R. Tygan.\n\nNote from Central: This shouldn't surprise you people, but unless you wanna turn your rifles into frag grenades, these new weapons use different ammunition from our mag rifles. Don’t mix this up if you value your lives."
UnlockedDescription="Prototype added to inventory"

[AdvancedCoilguns X2TechTemplate]
DisplayName="Advanced Coilguns"
CodeName="Firefox"
Summary="We can now turn our attention to developing specialized coil weaponry."
LongDescription="The challenges in adapting our new coilgun designs to fit our defined combat roles were not insignificant. While the reduced rate of fire offered by \"pure\" coilguns was never a concern for developing precision rifles, the coil groupings are. In addition, the coils themselves must be precisely machined and controlled so the ammunition does not cause a stovepipe malfunction, which could have disastrous consequences for the weapon and the user. Regardless, R&D's breakthroughs in magnetic technologies enable us to finally perfect the weapon action for our newest 8.6x70mm sniper rifle and combat shotgun designs.\n\nThis may explain why ADVENT never adopted this style of weaponry; they are too expensive and labor-intensive to produce, not exactly suited for industrial-scale production for a worldwide army of flash-trained clones. They are, however, an excellent fit for a small cadre of expert soldiers. Perhaps as technology marches on, we might be able to mass manufacture and arm larger numbers of soldiers and operatives with streamlined versions of linear induction weapons.\n\nAs for our observations of the general-purpose machine gun, we took what we learned developing the coil-rifle and multiplied it by at least sixteen times the detail and four times the size of a pre-war M249 SAW. What we did not initially suspect, however, is the unimaginable heat produced by our prototype when firing, to the point of a near-catastrophic failure of both the weapon and the firing range after its first few bursts.\n\nAnd thus, against many veterans' recommendations, we had to redesign our coil GPMG into a multi-barrel cannon with specialized recoil compensation and cooling apparatus for the operator's safety. While heavier than what our troops wanted, this is the best way to render the weapon safe while still maintaining effectiveness in the field. It is certain that Shen and I will redesign our LMG designs for better ergonomics right after completing this report, but our operatives will have to make due until then. R. Tygan"
UnlockedDescription="Prototype added to inventory"

[AutopsyDrone X2TechTemplate]
DisplayName="ADVENT Robotics"
CodeName="Duster"
Summary="ADVENT relies heavily on mechanized units for crowd control and warfare. While our specialists have a handle on infiltrating their programming, we have more work to do to fully understand the hardware they employ. We will start by dismantling the wreckage of ADVENT drones we have recovered in order to develop a general theory of ADVENT's construction and engineering processes."
LongDescription="We have achieved a rudimentary understanding of ADVENT's robotic combat systems. They are surprisingly much like our own pre-invasion designs, simply much more efficient with their power systems, and much more miniaturized overall. We view this project as a gateway to understanding ADVENT's more complex designs. R. Tygan." 

[AutopsyMutonElite X2TechTemplate]
DisplayName="Muton Elite Autopsy"
CodeName="Bluton"
Summary="This behemoth is different enough from other Mutons that it merits a specific investigation."
LongDescription="Central Officer Bradford previously mentioned old XCOM intelligence reports describing an elite form of Muton that served as a guardian to the Elders. This appears to be that form. The genetic enhancements extend into the creature's brain, suggesting improved pattern recognition and information processing in combat situations that are superior to the typical Muton. Additionally, the cadaver of this subject appears to have several cybernetic implants that boost the already extensive genetic modifications, some of which may be useful for our weapon development. I intend to let Shen investigate how to effectively make use of such systems, for my knowledge of cybernetics is far inferior to hers. R. Tygan.\n\nOne of the more exciting cybernetics found in this type of Muton appears grafted to its brain. Initial testing shows that it can track targets within full spherical vision. While a human brain cannot process full 360 degree information in real time, we can create a tracking system that can guide itself to a targeted area. Luckily, during XCOM's initial operations to prep the Avenger for real combat, I found several blueprints for a perfect Elerium-based warhead charge that our Technicals might make good use of. It'll take some time to miniaturize the implant, but we can make it work as the brain-computer interface components aren't needed for this use case.\n\nEven more surprisingly, we just took a scan of the Muton Elite's body armor and that gave me some ideas for improving our ballistic plating with the composite materials used in it. While we can't replicate the Muton's energy shield, we can come close enough with a \"carapace\" plating system. We can also use Dad's archives to make this work, as the original Alloy Carrier and TITAN-class armor prototypes can probably be used to adapt this technology to a modular design. Most likely we will need to tear the components out of Muton Elite corpses, but with enough supplies I can make our operatives survive a plasma bolt in the field. L. Shen."
AlertString="Muton Elite"

[AutopsyDrone X2TechTemplate]
DisplayName="ADVENT Robotics"
CodeName="Duster"
Summary="ADVENT relies heavily on mechanized units for crowd control and warfare. While our specialists have a handle on infiltrating their programming, we have more work to do to fully understand the hardware they employ. We will start by dismantling the wreckage of ADVENT drones we have recovered in order to develop a general theory of ADVENT's construction and engineering processes."
LongDescription="We have achieved a rudimentary understanding of ADVENT's robotic combat systems. They are surprisingly much like our own pre-invasion designs, simply much more efficient with their power systems, and much more miniaturized overall. We view this project as a gateway to understanding ADVENT's more complex designs. R. Tygan." 
AlertString="ADVENT Drone"

[GaussWeapons X2TechTemplate]
DisplayName="Advanced Magnetic Weaponry"
Summary="With our mastery of ADVENT's core weapons technology, we can now develop specialized weapon systems using the alien technology to improve on power storage and consumption, projectile path fidelity, and penetrative force over greater distances. We may be able to develop a sniper rifle, shotgun, and cannon variant based on our newly learned Magentic Weapons technology."
CodeName="Friedrich"
LongDescription="The fact that we now have access to advanced magnetic weaponry that is both combat effective and safe to operate at these power levels is quite an achievement. The overall design relies on advanced miniaturization technologies developed by the aliens which are, frankly, well beyond anything conceived of by Earth's leading military development firms at the time of the invasion. Despite our limited capability for extended test firings on board the ship, our latest prototypes are already capable of consistently accelerating an adaptive alloy projectile to over 5000 m/s in a simulated environment. We're still preparing the final assessment, but it is likely a field deployable unit would have to be limited to a lower power threshold due to the potential for ongoing strain to our troops when operating the weapons. R. Tygan."
UnlockedDescription="Prototype added to inventory"

